What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?

This data set contains 4,898 white wines with 11 variables on quantifying the chemical properties of each wine. At least 3 wine experts rated the quality of each wine, providing a rating between 0 (very bad) and 10 (very excellent). Our Guiding Question is which chemical properties influence the quality of white wines.

What other features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?

The variables fixed acidity, volatile acidity, citric acid, residual sugar, chlorides, density, free sulfur dioxide, total sulfur dioxide, pH, sulphates, alcohol all contribute to the better quality of white wines.

Density Versus Alcohol Plot

Bivariate Analysis

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?

I checked the correlation between alcohol variable and quality variable and found both variables to be strongly positively correlated. The correlation between the two variables alcohol and quality is 0.435547. On checking the correlation between chloride variable and quality, I found both variables to be weakly negatively correlated. The correlation between the two variables chlorides and quality is -0.2099344

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?

Another interesting relationship i observed is that, on plotting the alcohol variable against density, we observe a negative slope.

What was the strongest relationship you found?

The strongest relationship would be that alcohol content is a major factor that determines the quality of white wines. More investigations need to be done on this.

Multivariate Analysis

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. Were there features that strengthened each other in terms of looking at your feature(s) of interest?

Were there any interesting or surprising interactions between features?

From our first plot of density against alcohol we can observe that on wines with higher densities are rated poor while wines with lower densities are rated better in term of quality. It is also observed that wines rated poor have a lower alcohol content. Perhaps, our experts think that the more the alcohol in the wine, the better the wine served.

Reflection

The white wine dataset contains 11 distinct chemical properties of 4898 samples of wine as rated by 3 experts. Each of the wine sampled were rated on the quality of the wine. Our goal was to find which properties would most affect the quality of the wine. Checking the correlation between alcohol and the quality of wine, I observed that there was a strong positive correlation between the two variables. I visualized and the relationship between each variables with each other to see which would likely affect the quality of the wine rating
